name: integer_u16_binary16_max_safe_integer
description: |
  This is 2^11 - 1, the largest integer for which every integer through that
  magnitude is distinct in IEEE 754 binary16. The next integer is exactly
  representable but no longer safe because binary16 has only 11 bits of
  significand precision.
format: hex
decode-as: u16-le
pair:
  - with: binary16-exact-boundary.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u16"
  - "binary16"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "safe-integer"
  - "precision"
  - "boundary"
  - "off-by-one"
---
ff 07   # 2047 (2^11 - 1)
